<subSubSection id="2196265CBA3F30E4DED16BAF5AEA098A" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="61A3C301D01EFA146DCB9335AF2E76A1" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2756A1F1184C23EC467149DBB0673714" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="1E5626316C83826832347F90242E185F" class="Equisetopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Pseudobombax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="longiflorum">
<emphasis id="B6FB85B56A5194845C5D6CDD93C57FB5" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
<pageBreakToken id="7245194D9CA26E41B318795804F23C38" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" start="start">Pseudobombax</pageBreakToken>
longiflorum
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Mart.) A.Robyns by its long petiolules, obovate to suborbicular leaflets, and maculate seeds, but differing by the smaller leaves, flowers and fruits, slender branches, petioles 4 times the length of the petiolules (vs. a petiole/petiolule ratio of 6-12 in 
<taxonomicName id="285AD0C7CE0BECEEDA7038F7C8CCA9B0" class="Equisetopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Pseudobombax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="longiflorum">
<emphasis id="5784E09BFAFA2862E2199997B0B7AF8A" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Pseudobombax longiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and fruits acuminate for the distal 20% of their length (vs. 3%-5% in 
<taxonomicName id="6989D663B54BF2D8ECF46C69F03E322C" class="Equisetopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Pseudobombax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="longiflorum">
<emphasis id="CD1596D0F2FA62D363A852CCEB3BC6C8" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Pseudobombax longiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5603BBDA36A97D6D1B4E939821F69FE8" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" type="type">
